HEADWORD: Pseudorhabdite
<hw>Pseu`do*rhab"dite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Pseudo-</ets> + Gr. <?/ a rod.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>One of the peculiar rodlike corpuscles found in the integument of
certain Turbellaria. They are filled with a soft granular
substance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

